			<ns0:name>mseaborn@chromium.org</ns0:name><ns0:uri>/u/mseaborn@chromium.org/</ns0:uri></ns0:author><ns0:content type="html">Our intention is to produce a debug-mode-only syscall initially, so we don't need to freeze the ABI or foresee every possible extension.  Brad wants this for checking how much memory some apps consume, and how fragmented address space becomes.

In the long term it makes sense for NaCl to have an equivalent of Linux's /proc/self/maps, Windows's VirtualQuery() and OS X's mach_vm_region().</ns0:content><ns0:updated>2013-04-03T20:07:53.000Z</ns0:updated><ns0:published>2013-04-03T20:07:53.000Z</ns0:published><ns2:updates /><ns0:title>Comment 2 by mseaborn@chromium.org</ns0:title><ns0:link href="http://code.google.com/p/nativeclient/issues/detail?id=3366#c2" rel="alternate" type="text/html" /><ns0:link href="https://code.google.com/feeds/issues/p/nativeclient/issues/3366/comments/full/2" rel="self" type="application/atom+xml" /></ns0:entry>